quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  44,17,"And certainly We tried before them the people of Pharaoh, and there came to them a noble Messenger"
  44,18,"Saying, \"Deliver to me the servants of Allah; surely I am a trustworthy messenger unto you"
  44,19,"And be not arrogant against Allah, for I come with clear authority"
  44,20,And surely I have taken refuge with my Lord and your Lord against your stoning me to death
  44,21,"And if you put no faith in me, then let me go"
  44,22,"Then he called upon his Lord, \"These are a guilty people"
  44,23,"(The reply came,) \"So go forth with My servants by night; for surely you will be pursued"
  44,24,And leave the sea divided (as a furrow); surely they are a host that shall be drowned
  44,25,How many are the gardens and springs they have left behind
  44,26,And corn fields and noble places
  44,27,And goodly things wherein they rejoiced
  44,28,"Thus it was, and We gave them as a heritage to another people"
  44,29,"So the heaven and the earth did not weep for them, nor were they respited"
  44,30,And certainly We delivered the children of Israel from the abasing chastisement
  44,31,"From Pharaoh; surely he was haughty, (and) one of those who committed excesses"
  44,32,"And certainly We chose them, knowingly (or purposely), above all the nations"
  44,33,And We gave them signs wherein was a clear trial
  44,34,Lo! These (the pagan Arabs) say
  44,35,There is naught but our first death and we shall not be raised again
  44,36,"Bring back our fathers, if you are truthful"
  44,37,"What! Are they better than the people of Tubba and those before them? We destroyed them, for surely they were guilty"
  44,38,And We did not create the heavens and the earth and what is between them in sport
  44,39,"We create them both not, except with truth, but most of them know not"
  44,40,Assuredly the Day of Decision (or of Sorting) is the term appointed for all of them
  44,41,"The day on which friend can in naught avail friend, nor can they be helped"
  44,42,Save those on whom Allah has mercy; surely He is the Mighty the Merciful
  44,43,Behold the tree of Zaqqum
  44,44,Is the food of the sinful
  44,45,"Like molten brass, it shall boil in (their) bellies"
  44,46,Like the seesing of boiling water
  44,47,"(It will be said,) \"Seize him, then drag him down into the midst of hell"
  44,48,Then pour above his head of the torment of the boiling water
  44,49,"Saying, ´Taste; lo! You were forsooth the mighty, the noble"
  44,50,´Surely this is what you used to doubt!´
  44,51,Surely the righteous are in a secure place
  44,52,Amidst Gardens and springs
  44,53,"Attired in fine silk and rich brocade, face to face"
  44,54,"Thus shall it be, and We will join them with Houris (pure and beautiful companions) with wide, lovely eyes"
  44,55,They shall call in safety therein for every fruit
  44,56,"They taste not death therein except the first death (i.e. in this physical life), and He will have saved them from the doom of hell"
  44,57,A grace from your Lord; this is the supreme achievement (or triumph)
  44,58,Verily We have made it (the Quran) easy in your tongue that they may be mindful
  44,59,Therefore wait (O Muhammad); they too are waiting
  45,1,Ha Mim
  45,2,"The revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise"
  45,3,Most surely in the heavens and the earth there are signs for the believers
  45,4,And in your own creation and in what He spreads abroad of animals there are signs for a people that have faith
  45,5,"And in the variation of the night and the day, and in the sustenance Allah sends down from the clouds, then gives life thereby to the earth after its death, and in the changing of the winds, there are signs for a people who understand"
  45,6,These are the Signs of Allah which We recite to you with Truth; then in what explanations would they believe after (rejecting) Allah and His Signs
  45,7,Woe to every sinful dealer in falsehood
  45,8,"Who hears the Signs of Allah recited to him, then persists proudly as though he had not heard them; so announce to him a grievous punishment"
  45,9,"And when he comes to know of any of Our revelations, he takes it for a jest; these it is that shall have abasing doom"
  45,10,"Before them is Hell, and there shall not avail them aught of what they earned, nor those whom they took for guardians besides Allah, and they shall have an awful doom"
  45,11,"This is guidance; and as for those who disbelieve in the revelations of their Lord, they shall have a painful penalty because of their abominations"